content.description:
ISU Guide: ***

Crux was near the top of the climb.
content.protection: 5 bolts up the crack to chain anchors

content.description: Tricky moves off the ground, slightly easier than Tricks ...?
content.protection: 4 bolts, sport anchors.  Shares anchors with Tricks Ain't For Kids.
content.location: The rightmost of two 12s at the right end of the Red Light District.

content.description: Mountaineering flavor with moves punctuated by ledges and deep clefts, upper third is a fun, challenging overhanging dihedral.
content.protection: 12 bolts, sport anchors. Just possible to get off with a 60M rope, 70M recommeneded.

content.description: Excellent thin, technical face.  Hard pull off the ground and stays that way.
content.protection: 4 bolts, sport anchors.  Shares top anchors with What A Climb, Max!.
content.location: Right of Layback and Enjoy.  Also, the leftmost of two 12s at the right end of the Red Light District.

content.description: Leftmost route on the left side of the Red Light District and approximately at the highest section of the crag.  Steep section and ledges.
content.protection: 12 bolts, sport anchors. Just possible to get off with a 60M rope, 70M recommeneded.
content.location: Leftmost route on the left side of the Red Light District.

content.description: A lttle right of Sweaty Betty, is another bolt line.
content.location: Sweaty Betty and Tension Forever (right) are two routes close together with a short broken section on either side.

content.description: Route the start between blunt prow and arete to the right.
content.location: Right of Private Dancer.

content.description: Starts on "coral lava" ledge, up overhanging white dihedral on steep and powerful moves.
content.location: After a short broken section, Sweaty Betty is the leftmost route.

content.description: Blunt arete start.
content.location: Right of The Tease.

content.description: Bolts up brown "hourglass" face, then same finish Slam Bam ...
content.location: Right of Slam Bam ..., shares top anchors with Slam Bam ...

content.description: Thin dihedral start with thin finger jams lead to edges and easier but fun climbing to the top.
content.protection: 5 bolts, sport anchors.  Also, easily led on cams and maybe a nut or two.

content.description: An okay route that starts up a slabby scoop and finishes on some nice pockets.
content.protection: 6 bolts to a two bolt anchor.
content.location: Far let end of The Red Light District just right of Twisted.

content.description: Start on slabby brown rock that steepens to a bulge at the top.
content.location: Right of Woody in the Woods.

content.description: Short blocky section leads to great looking right facing dihedral with fun jug hauling on big edges and pockets.
content.location: Right of Kinky.

content.description: Stout pockets at the crux.
content.location: Leftmost route of the tall, east facing middle section of the Red Light District.

content.description: Short route left of a blunt prow.
content.location: Right of Hollow Weenie.

content.description: Work through a pumpy flake/bulge about mid-climb.
content.location: Right of No Hips...

content.description: Shares a move or two with Love Canal.
content.location: Right of Love Canal.

content.description: Same first 3 bolts as Immaculate Deception then up right leaning dihedral.
content.location: Shares start with Immaculate Deception, branch right after 3rd bolt.

content.description: Climb a short thin, fingery corner to a ledge (probably the crux). Continue up hueco'd rock until a big roof.  Pass the roof on the left and gun for the top anchors.
content.location: Just to the right of Girly Mon.

content.description: Short but worthy route starts with a tough pull at the start. The climb eases towards the top.
content.location: Above a broken section near the ground is a short high cliff band with 3 routes. With no nice approach from the ground, it is equipped to rappel into the generous ledge below the 3 steep routes. This is the leftmost of the 3 routes.

content.description: White face with thin moves.
content.location: Downhill and 50 feet right of Sweaty Betty/Tension Forever.

content.description: Difficult short, brown prow.
content.location: Right of Lip Service.

content.description: At the first bolt, most people move left into the short blocky corner, its possible to boulder problem over the first bolt to the ledge.  From the ledge follow a steep right leaning corner.  Finish on pumpy, steep two and three finger pockets.
content.location: Right of Love Slave/Barbara Dare.

content.description: Up a nice face and continue up with nice sections punctuated with small ledges.  This route and Trundler are likely the tallest 5.8's at Massacre where 5.8s are less than 2% of the 750 routes.
content.protection: 12 bolts, sport anchors.  Just possible to get off with a 60M rope, 70M recommeneded.
content.location: Right of Trundler.

content.description: Tough moves letting up for a cruise to the top.
content.location: Above a broken section near the ground is a short high cliff band with 3 routes. With no nice approach from the ground, it is equipped to rappel into the generous ledge below the 3 steep routes. This is the rightmost of the 3 routes.

content.description: Several variations.
content.location: Right most of this cluster of routes in the middle section of the Red Light District.  There is a short broken section between Boy Toy and Sweaty Betty.

content.description: Fun, sustained for the grade.
content.location: Above a broken section near the ground is a short high cliff band with 3 routes. With no nice approach from the ground, it is equipped to rappel into the generous ledge below the 3 steep routes. This is the middle route of the 3.

content.description: Climb up the short blocky section of Love Slave. Move right to and up the prox.  Finish left to the top anchors of Love Slave.
content.protection: 6 bolts, sport anchors.  Same top anchors as Love Slave.
content.location: Shares start and top anchors with Love Slave.

content.description: Pull up onto the arete then move slightly left connecting steep pockets to a ramp.  Climb straight up the headwall block to a stance the top anchors.
content.location: Starts 6 feet right of Scared Stiff.
